properties.description: In method overriding, the relevant method definition is replaced in the derived class, which changes the method behavior. When it comes to method overloading, a method is created with the same name and is in the same class while having different signatures.

Gives developers an option to define declarative tags on a few entities. For instance, class and method are known as attributes. The information related to the attribute can be retrieved during runtime by taking the help of Reflection.
Once you understand the syntax, your next step would be to learn about branching and looping statements. Loops, in particular, help you in creating programs that require repetitive tasks.

maintenance.description: The kitchen faucet has been leaking constantly, wasting water and causing dampness under the sink.
Window in the living room cracked after a storm, needs replacement for safety and insulation.
The electrical outlet in the bedroom stopped working suddenly. No power when devices are plugged in.
The AC unit isn't cooling properly despite being set to the lowest temperature. Makes strange noises when running.
The garage door opener remote stopped working. The door can only be operated manually now.
Black mold has appeared on the bathroom ceiling and walls, especially around the shower area.
The garbage disposal is making humming noise but not grinding. Likely something stuck in the mechanism.
